N2  - This study questions traditional assumptions linking organizational career assistance programs with increased employee satisfaction with and commitment to organizations. A model of individual career thinking is proposed in which a match between individual and organizational career plans is the primary determinant of satisfaction and remaining with art organization. Evidence from 266 individuals supports the influence of such matching and suggests revisions of the model.
